# l2switch — Two-Port MAC-Learning L2 Switch (DPDK)
gcc -O3 -march=native switch.c -o switch $(pkg-config --cflags --libs libdpdk)
A minimal but production-correct L2 switch that reproduces the core of the
official `l2fwd` sample while wiring in `rte_hash` for MAC learning and
`rte_timer` for entry aging.

---

## Topology

```
  NIC port 0                           NIC port 1
  ──────────┐                        ┌──────────
  host A    │◄──── l2switch ────────►│  host B
  ──────────┘                        └──────────
```

Packets arriving on port 0 are forwarded to port 1, and vice versa.

---

## Data-Plane Pipeline (per packet)

```
rte_eth_rx_burst(port)
        │
        ▼
   ┌────────────┐
   │ Learn src  │  mac_learn(src_mac → ingress_port)
   │  MAC       │  rte_hash_add_key() → positional slot
   └─────┬──────┘
         │
         ▼
   ┌─────────────┐
   │ Lookup dst  │  rte_hash_lookup(dst_mac)
   │  MAC        │  hit  → use stored egress port
   └─────┬───────┘  miss → flood (send to other port)
         │
         ▼
   ┌─────────────┐
   │ Hair-pin    │  drop if dst_port == ingress_port
   │  guard      │
   └─────┬───────┘
         │
         ▼
rte_eth_tx_burst(egress_port)
```

send_pkt generates packets by the help of scapy.
